2.5 years later we are back to the old ways. If you want to sustain in this profession, my advice would be to use this opportunity well to master the art of selling options during low vix. Don't wait for the high premiums to comeback. It might take a while.

Had tough time in the first half of 2020, where the old ways suddenly stopped working. Because of the high Vix, there were random IV spikes & fast crush happening all around. That's the time when had to shift to directional trading & completely revamp my trading for the better.

Volatility is more predictable when Vix is low. My max experience in option selling is when Vix is <15. As directional opportunities reduce, one needs to objectively follow the falling, rising & stagnant IVs for neutral setups. Doing that it becomes possible to avoid an IV spike.
